    "givenName": "Florian_Volery",
    "motivations": "My motivation for becoming a DRep stems from a decade-long career in Swiss banking and my work on the Liqwid protocol, where I lead a team developing cutting-edge blockchain solutions that drive real-world economic impact. \n\nHaving experienced the inefficiencies and limitations of traditional financial systems, I am passionate about the transformative power of DeFi to reshape finance as we know it. I want to bring my personal and professional experiences to the Cardano community, using them to support initiatives that will drive meaningful change. \n\nAs someone deeply invested in the growth of the Cardano blockchain, I’m eager to take on a more active role in shaping its future by empowering projects that align with long-term value creation and the advancement of decentralized financial systems.",
    "objectives": "As a DRep, my primary objective is to advocate for solutions that bridge decentralized finance (DeFi) and traditional finance (TradFi) by leveraging my expertise in both fields. I want also to represent the builders and support them creating value for the Cardano ecosystem.\n\nI firmly believe in the potential of blockchain technology to revolutionize the financial system, making it more transparent, efficient, and accessible to all. My aim is to support proposals that promote real-world adoption of blockchain solutions, particularly those increasing the user adoption of the Cardano network.\n\nI want to contribute to the strategic direction of Cardano, ensuring that its ecosystem continues to lead innovation in decentralized finance while maintaining the principles of transparency, security, and sustainability.",
